"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-bmx-silver-medal-kieran-reillyteam-b1174027.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the search feature\", \"from\": 7, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"your consent\", \"from\": 35, \"to\": 47}, {\"ngram\": \"cookies\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"similar technologies\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"search\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our privacy policy\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 205}, {\"ngram\": \"more information\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics In the end, the man with the accidental mullet came up just short in his quest for gold as Kieran Reilly had to settle for silver in the BMX freestyle.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 336, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"score\": 0.9972444810813649, \"rank\": 0.002753795082536723, \"text\": \"Kieran\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\"}, {\"begin\": 382, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999999990095603, \"rank\": 9.904159793032964e-10, \"text\": \"BMX freestyle\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 254}, {\"ngram\": \"the man\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 263}, {\"ngram\": \"the accidental mullet\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"his quest\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 331}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was originally a haircut gone wrong but Reilly kept it anyway, rode at the World Championships and won gold.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a haircut\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 425}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It became his lucky charm for every competition since but wasn't quite enough to give him the gold on the biggest stage, the Olympics, denied by a single point by the Argentinian Jose Torres Gil.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 678, \"end\": 689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9736705166674555, \"rank\": 0.01860489730872346, \"text\": \"Argentinian\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joey_Torres\", \"score\": 0.9999999085039277, \"rank\": 9.149597237084035e-08, \"text\": \"Jose Torres\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joey_Torres\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joey_Torres\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his lucky charm\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"every competition\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest stage\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"a single point\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 670}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reilly felt like he'd done enough to win on his Games debut lifting his hands aloft in celebration but then the doubts came in, gesticulating in prayer that the judges landed on his side.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his Games\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"his hands\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"the doubts\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"prayer\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"the judges\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 875}, {\"ngram\": \"his side\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 894}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He improved on his first-round score but he could not better Gil's first outing and one of the earliest of the hour-long competition.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his first-round score\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"Gil's first outing\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"the hour-long competition\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It marked the latest chapter in the journey of the Gateshead lad, who grew up with a football field and skatepark just outside his front door.\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the latest chapter\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"the journey\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gateshead lad\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"a football field\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"his front door\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the age of nine, after years of imploring, his parents bought him his first BMX bike and he likened it to love at first sight, initially making a name for himself with YouTube clips and then shining in competitions, most notably the World Championships.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX_bike\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BMX bike\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX_bike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX_bike\"}, {\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 0.9999999939723239, \"rank\": 6.0276308591326e-09, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1207}, {\"ngram\": \"imploring\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1220}, {\"ngram\": \"his parents\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1233}, {\"ngram\": \"first sight\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1393}, {\"ngram\": \"most notably the World Championships\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In scorching heat, he did well to complete two high-scoring rounds in the 93s.\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"heat\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"two high-scoring rounds\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1500}, {\"ngram\": \"the 93s\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, French favourite Anthony Jeanjean, usually so reliable, fell on his opening run and, while he moved into the bronze medal position, he hung his head in his hands as the outcome of the competition became official in front of his home crowd.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8682496021041217, \"rank\": 0.1326009275880295, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"his opening run\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal position\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1657}, {\"ngram\": \"his head\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"his hands\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"the outcome\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"his home crowd\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1765}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were a number of fallers, among them the defending champion Logan Martin from Australia, who ended up well outside the medal positions.\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"score\": 0.867944397881412, \"rank\": 0.15214300855970625, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 1852, \"end\": 1861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.9582034383576172, \"rank\": 0.03584657578255346, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.